Karana Server</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirderekdrygon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Derek Drygon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/19/02 12:04:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=153.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://champions.morpheus.net/pics/derek2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drop rates in HoT</span><hr size=1> My guild has been doing the halls of testing for a few months now and have only recieved 1 plate BP and 1 robe.  We have only got 1 pair of plate leggings, and no other type of leggings at all.  So far we have only done the entrence area before doze's room.  The only reason we haven't moved is because the entrence to the HoT is very easy to get to, and we dont need a mage to get people in (we have a low number of mages in the guild)<br>
<br>
I have heard rumors that the drop rates change as you get deeper in the zone.   According to some people I have spoken with, it seems that more brestplates and legs drop near the exit area of the halls of testing.   I was wondering if anyone might be able to confirm, deny, or post your personal experiences here in regards to this.   I dont necessaraly need raw hardcore facts, speculation is fine so long as its educated and based off of observations.<br>
<br>
Any info would be much appreciated!<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Sir Derek Drygon<br>
59th rank Knight of Truth<br>
Champions of Norrath<br>
The Rathe <p>"Hear it not Heaven thine ministers have done it!"
