<br>Crusader for Brell
<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker
</bold>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzerger66.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zerger66</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/20/02 2:19:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=153.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drop rates in HoT</span><hr size=1> Kinda off the topic since I will talk about Kael Arena...<br>
<br>
Anyways, we got an insane amount of Silk all the time and hardly anything else.<br>
<br>
We got like <br>
3 Silk robes<br>
1 Plate BP<br>
no other BPs <br>
so far.<br>
<br>
During our last raid we got around <br>
15 silk pieces (including 2 robes and legs)<br>
5 chain (Boots, legs, gaunts)<br>
3 leather (legs, bracer, helm)<br>
3 plate (2 boots, 1 gaunts) <br>
<br>
I know Kael Arena isnt compareable to HoT, but after all, its the same kinda game. <br>
<br>
We had many pissed plate classes and 3 overly happy silky guys. And that went over 2 days.<br>
<br>
Really strange.<br>
<br>
By the way, we never got a lotof plate, ever.<br>
Well do that boring chanterhouse for a while soon to equip the tanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uloreinsolamnus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lorein Solamnus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/21/02 1:50:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=153.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drop rates in HoT</span><hr size=1> To answer the question about whether the drop rates change while you move closer to the exit or not, I haven't observed a significant change in it. What I have observed is that in the two past months we seem to be getting fewer drops in general. We might just have been unlucky on our last trips, but whereas at times we got 25 drops, now we get 8-10.<br>
As far as the actual drops go, we seem to be getting lots of plate and silk and less chain to be followed by leather in the end. What's interesting is that I have seen quite a few silk robes and many pairs of plate legs drop, but only a couple of plate helms and gaunts that other people here mentioned they see a lot. Very common for us are silk boots and guants and those leather gloves that noone wants. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhakashakamalakabalsaka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haka Shakamalakabalsaka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 267<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/21/02 2:42:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=153.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drop rates in HoT</span><hr size=1> Hot Last night:<br>
