<br>
I was fortunate enough to receive plate helm, boots, and legs this weekend! Yay! <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Baron Varner Rapscallion</a> 
<br>Crusader for Brell
<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker
</bold>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uraynoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raynoc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 134<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/23/02 8:33:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=153.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~suretang/images/usf2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drop rates in HoT</span><hr size=1> Plate always drops good in Hot.<br>
<br>
Which like others have stated..You need more plate since so many classes use it compated to the other ones.<br>
<br>
The one we always had problems dropping for us was Leather.<br>
Sure we would get a leather cap ,  bracer etc here and there..but it took months for a leather bp to drop.<br>
<br>
A few legs and stuff here and there, but damn the Leather bp was rare as hell. <br>
<br>
All in all HoT is so random...Some days we would get 30+ drops in like 4 hrs and other times we would get less then 10 for the same amount of time.<br>
<br>
Just keep farming ,  Get as much as ya can and mq the extras to support the Price of Peridots!<br>
<br>
